    "output": "The time of flight for a projectile launched with an initial velocity $v_0$ and angle $\theta_0$ is given by the equation ${T}_{\text{tof}}=\frac{2({v}_{0}\text{sin}{Î¸}_{0})}{g}$. This can be derived by considering the vertical motion of the projectile, where the maximum height is reached when the vertical velocity component is zero, and the total time of flight is twice the time to reach the maximum height."
