  {
    "instruction": "What is the equation for the trajectory of a projectile?",
    "input": "",
    "output": "The trajectory of a projectile launched with an initial velocity $v_0$ and angle $\theta_0$ is given by the equation $y=(\text{tan}{Î¸}_{0})xâ[\frac{g}{2{({v}_{0}\text{cos}{Î¸}_{0})}^{2}}]{x}^{2}$. This equation relates the vertical position $y$ to the horizontal position $x$ of the projectile, taking into account the effects of gravity."
